---  
description: Use when creating datasource folder templates, datasource content folders, shared or local datasources, or debugging datasource picker issues.  
alwaysApply: false  
---  
  
Datasource structure has two parts:  
  
1. Folder template  
- Create under `/sitecore/templates/Project/<site-collection>/Folders/`  
- Add `__Standard Values`  
- Set `__Masters` to allowed datasource template IDs  
  
2. Folder instance  
- Create under `/sitecore/content/<site-collection>/<site-name>/Data/`  
- Use the folder template  
- This must exist or the datasource picker will be empty  
  
Patterns:  
- Shared datasource folder: `/sitecore/content/<site-collection>/<site-name>/Data/<ComponentFolder>/`  
- Page-local datasource folder: `/sitecore/content/<site-collection>/<site-name>/Home/<page>/Data/`  
  
List component rules:  
- Parent datasource item lives inside the folder instance  
- Child datasource items live under the parent datasource item  
- Parent template should inherit `_HorizonDatasourceGrouping`  
- Parent template standard values should set `__Masters` to child template IDs  
  
Always check:  
- Folder template exists  
- Folder instance exists  
- Datasource items exist inside the folder instance  
- Rendering `Datasource Location` query matches the folder template name exactly  